snippet.title: Data Preparation in ML.NET: Select, Drop, Take, Shuffle, and Filter
snippet.description:
Data preparation is important to get your data in a workable state for it to work in a machine learning algorithm. This video will show how to select columns, drop columns, take rows, shuffle rows, and filter rows in ML.NET to start preparing your data.

Code - https://github.com/jwood803/MLNetExamples/blob/master/MLNetExamples/DataPrepRowsColumns/Program.cs

snippet.title: ML Net Tutorial 2 -  Predicting Prices Using Regression Analysis
snippet.description:
This is a complete ML.Net Tutorial with C# and Visual Studio from the scratch.
Procedure and Source codes here: https://www.datarmatics.com/data-science/2019/10/05/ml-net-tutorial-2-predicting-prices-using-regression-analysis/

Tutorial 1 here: https://youtu.be/dWq6Xmz5aXg

TensorFlow Tutorials: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLMz1vLpcJgGCPONANPZymB1l6W9PzLzy5

Steps
1. Understand Your Dataset
2. Create a Console Application in Visual Studio
3. Create the Classes
4. Define the Data and Model Paths
5. Create a Machine Learning Context
6. Load the Data
7. Create a Learning Pipeline
8. Train and Save the Model
9. Make Prediction
